    ! sin(x)/x Taylor coefficients as DD pairs: c(k) = (-1)^k / (2k+1)!
    ! 13 terms cover |x| <= pi/8 to ~2^-115 (well below DD epsilon). 10
    ! terms leave a truncation error of ~1e-24 at x² ≈ (π/8)² ≈ 0.154,
    ! which propagates through the Newton steps in asin/acos/atan and
